('1ea77086-6d1c-58e3-a032-af2ec6102536', '02713a3e-ded7-4f5d-8e3c-ff77f8e796b6', 95, 'Senior RPLS LESTER JOSEPH STANGER (license #2111, granted 1979); est. age ~77 (license_tenure_proxy assuming typical RPLS-earn age of 30 — TX RPLS requires 4yr college + 4yr supervised survey-in-training + state exam); firm tenure 47yr. Second RPLS ROBERT SHANE NEALLY (granted 2000, est. age ~56).', 75, '47yr-tenured firm with 4 active RPLS — TX RPLS license is a 4yr-college + 4yr-apprentice + exam-gated skilled-trade moat; firm passes the >5yr in-business hard gate; vertical has documented recurring B2B from oil/gas ROW + construction stake-out + ALTA + FEMA elev certs. Default L2 mid-range pending enrichment-time confirmation of staff count + recurring program mix (homebuilder logos / MSA language).', 45, 'Long tenure (47yr) suggests classic exit-window — owner is operationally entrenched but at natural retirement age. (Default scoring — confirm individual coasting tells at enrichment-time live-fetch.)', 67, 'TX secondary metro (Tyler, Smith County) — moderate transactional volume; recurring B2B drives valuation. LOW-PE-ATTENTION vertical: only Bowman (NASDAQ:BWMN) + Westwood (Endeavour Capital) are PE-backed rollup platforms in TX; large-AEC strategics (Stantec, WSP, AECOM, Kimley-Horn, Cobb Fendley, LJA) only bolt-on $5M+ rev firms — sub-$5M independents are structurally under-targeted. ETA/search-fund appetite emerging fast 2024-2026 (top-15 vertical in Stanford Search Fund Study). +2 baseline boost for solo/2-RPLS metros = opportunity zone.', 71, 'B_forward', 'Senior RPLS LESTER JOSEPH STANGER (granted 1979, est. age ~77 via license_tenure_proxy, 47yr firm tenure); STANGER SURVEYING TYLER, LLC in Tyler, Smith County. 4-RPLS firm. L1 95 / L2 75 / L3 45 / L4 67 → final 71, tier B_forward. LOW-PE-ATTENTION vertical: only Bowman + Westwood active in TX surveying-firm PE rollup; sub-$5M independent universe is structurally under-targeted. Forward to ETA/search-fund community.', 'A